GHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: TM does not reduce damage taken</span><hr size=1> Okay I ran some new tests for this.<br>
<br>
I had a warrior duel me, he kept attack off as the one I dueled did before, this time I did not have him use /furious. Instead I just attacked him for a couple minutes while he stood there facing me. I used low damage/low delay weaps for max number of hits between heals (had a druid keeping him alive for the duration).<br>
<br>
Well I have some bad news, he does INDEED get a swingback for every riposte I TM through.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Natural Riposte:<br>
[Sun Dec 15 07:37:14 2002] Tiarnan tries to pierce YOU, but misses!<br>
[Sun Dec 15 07:37:14 2002] You try to slash Tiarnan, but Tiarnan ripostes!<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->This is the standard riposte. I did not score a TM success and he riposted and had a swingback as expected.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>TM'd Riposte:<br>
[Sun Dec 15 07:36:44 2002] Tiarnan tries to pierce YOU, but misses!<br>
[Sun Dec 15 07:36:44 2002] You slash Tiarnan for 18 points of damage.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->This is the type of riposte I was on the lookout for. The only reason he'd have tried to pierce me was if he was riposteing my hit. As you can see I hit him for 18 points and he tried to hit me back for that hit. This is actually a riposted hit that I TM'd through and he scored a swingback for.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>TM'd Riposte - I missed:<br>
[Sun Dec 15 07:38:43 2002] Tiarnan pierces YOU for 19 points of damage.<br>
[Sun Dec 15 07:38:43 2002] You try to slash Tiarnan, but miss!<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->This is the 3rd type of riposte, I TM'd through his riposte, but I actually missed him after bypassing his riposte. He still gets a swingback for this, since his riposte is occuring BEFORE there is a check to see whether I land a hit or not.<br>
<br>
I'd say this proves to me that regardless if your enemy is enraged or not, you will get hit back on all ripostes, TM'd or not.<br>
<br>
Simply put, a riposte is a riposte. Your enemy swings at you no matter what on a riposte and Tactical Mastery just allows you to get your hits through the block portion of the riposte but doesn't negate the swingback. Which is a big dissapointment. <br>
<br>
The only way this test would prove false would be if there were different rules for players and mobs on ripostes, but I doubt mobs follow a different rule for these.<br>
<br>
